## TIPS FOR BEST RESULTS

|Tip                                 |Detail                                                                                                            |
|------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|**Paste context forward**           |Each prompt has a `<PASTE_..._HERE>` block. Always paste prior findings. Claude CLI has no memory between runs.   |
|**Run from project root**           |Claude CLI automatically indexes files in the current directory.                                                  |
|**Point explicitly at `ok/` folder**|Add `"The JSON config files are in the ok/ subdirectory."` to any prompt if auto-detection misses them.           |
|**Save every output**               |Redirect to `.txt` files. You’ll need them for later prompts.                                                     |
|**Iterate on Prompt 3**             |The Pandas audit is the highest-value prompt. If it misses something, rerun with `"Focus specifically on file X"`.|
|**Use `--max-tokens`**              |For prompts 5–7 that generate code, add `--max-tokens 8000` to the CLI command.                                   |
|**Ask for line numbers**            |If a finding is vague, follow up with `"Show me the exact file and line number for [finding]"`.                   |